 of anything whether you have Innate Defense 5 or not.  When I'm dead running naked I sure don't notice stability 3 negating anything but agility 3 still works fine.  If a mob is hitting you for max easily then having an extra 5 or 10% bonus to mitigate isn't going to suddenly make the mob fail to land max on a regular basis.  I suspect the 1800 AC that Furor talks about is the amount of AC you need before it becomes hard for a PoP uber to hit you for full, and at that point I'm sure the mitigation bonuses will be very helpful.  But if you can't get that kind of AC, might as well stick with agility line which always work no matter what AC you have.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is get a feel of how easily it is for a mob to hit you for max before deciding whether you want to get mitigation or agility.  If the mobs aren't hitting you for max often, then mitigation helps.  We know for sure that you can always mitigate better when you're ahead (i.e. green hits can be mitigated to nothing).  But if the mob is ahead of you (hit you for max easily), then you have to get more AC before mitigation AAs will matter. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=haass>Haass</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 802<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/19/03 3:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2403.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_ale.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Combat Agility = Combat Stability</span><hr size=1> Jesus christ, this is still on the first page ....<br>
