<br>
We just went over this.  You didn't find anything new, and you're wrong.  CA &gt; CS, period.  No matter what new descriptions you want to read, it still doesn't change the facts.  CS doesn't lower a mobs max or minimum hit, which means you're still taking damage bonus from said mob.  You also are taking any contact procs or stuns the mob may incur upon you.  While both are worth getting, CA is definitely a better skill than CS. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=48986">Marshall Haass Wolvesbane</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=71943">Venerable Cagna Soulshaker</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
